ZH: 我只是一个旁观者，不敢插手他们的争执。
EN: I am just an onlooker and don't dare to intervene in their argument.

ZH: 他坐在一旁观看着比赛。
EN: He sat on the sidelines and watched the game.

ZH: 每次发生事故，总有人选择旁观而不是帮助。
EN: Whenever an accident occurs, there are always people who choose to be bystanders instead of offering help.

ZH: 在这个纷争中，我决定保持旁观。
EN: In this dispute, I decided to remain a spectator.

ZH: 他喜欢旁观人们的对话，而不参与其中。
EN: He enjoys observing people's conversations without getting involved.

ZH: 作为一个旁观者，我不了解内情。
EN: As an onlooker, I don't know the inside story.

ZH: 这场争端我决定只是一个旁观者。
EN: I decided to be just a bystander in this dispute.

ZH: 我不想成为这个问题的旁观者，我要积极参与。
EN: I don't want to be a spectator to this problem, I want to actively participate.

ZH: 他站在街角，旁观着人们匆匆而过。
EN: He stood on the street corner, observing people hurrying by.

ZH: 她默默地旁观着，不发表任何意见。
EN: She silently observed, without expressing any opinions.

ZH: 当我在街上旁观时，我看到了一场车祸。
EN: When I was observing on the street, I witnessed a car accident.

ZH: 他的行为让我感到愤怒，我无法旁观。
EN: His actions made me angry, I couldn't stand by and watch.

ZH: 她总是喜欢旁观别人的成功，却对自己的事情漠不关心。
EN: She always likes to be a spectator of other people's success but is indifferent to her own affairs.

ZH: 我们不能只是作为旁观者，而应该积极参与社会问题的解决。
EN: We can't just be bystanders, we should actively participate in solving social problems.

ZH: 如果我们只是旁观者，这个团队永远不会成功。
EN: If we are just spectators, this team will never succeed.

ZH: 我决定站出来，不再成为社会问题的旁观者。
EN: I decided to step forward and no longer be a bystander to social problems.

ZH: 很多人倾向于袖手旁观，而不是帮助别人。
EN: Many people tend to stand by and do nothing instead of helping others.

ZH: 在她孤立无援的时候，他选择了旁观。
EN: When she was left helpless, he chose to remain on the sidelines.

ZH: 当我发现犯罪行为时，我不能成为旁观者。
EN: When I witness a criminal act, I cannot be a bystander.

ZH: 在这个大问题面前，我们不能保持旁观的态度。
EN: In the face of this major issue, we cannot remain indifferent.

ZH: 有些人不愿参与争执，只是选择旁观。
EN: Some people prefer not to get involved in arguments and choose to be spectators.
